com.paypal.selion.configuration

Class ListenerInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paypal.selion.configuration.ListenerInfo

  • public class ListenerInfo
extends Object
    ListenerInfo serves as a utility to store information pertaining to a Listener, used by ListenerManager.registerListener(ListenerInfo) .

    • Constructor Detail

      • ListenerInfo

        public ListenerInfo(Class<?> className,
                    String jvmArgToParse)
        Saves information about listener class which is enabled/disabled per its VM argument. When VM argument for the listener is not defined, the listener is enabled by system default.
        Parameters:
        className - - The Class name.
        jvmArgToParse - - The JVM argument that should be read to decide if the listener is to be enabled/disabled.

      • ListenerInfo

        public ListenerInfo(Class<?> className,
                    String jvmArgToParse,
                    boolean defaultStateWhenNotDefined)
        Saves information about listener class which is enabled/disabled per its VM argument. When VM argument is not defined, whether it is enabled/disabled is decided by the caller via (@code defaultStateWhenNotDefined}.
        Parameters:
        className - - The Class name.
        jvmArgToParse - - The JVM argument that should be read to decide whether the listener is to be enabled/disabled.
        defaultStateWhenNotDefined - - The default boolean for whether enabled/disabled when the JVM argument is not defined.
